  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_394214969" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/394214969" />
    <a title="Lyn Elliott" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/10312986-lyn-elliott"><img alt="Lyn Elliott" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1377589438p2/10312986.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/394214969?book_show_action=true">Aug 17, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Lyn Elliott" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Lyn Elliott" href="/user/show/10312986-lyn-elliott">Lyn Elliott</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780805208986" href="/book/show/64533.The_Crusades_Through_Arab_Eyes">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/10312986-lyn-elliott?shelf=history">history</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/10312986-lyn-elliott?shelf=translation">translation</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/10312986-lyn-elliott?shelf=middle-east">middle-east</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer394214969" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12993739916178499172">Amin Maalouf is one of my favourite writers. Born in Lebanon, he lives in France and writes in French. His fiction and nonfiction alike are concerned with tolerance, intolerance, culture and civilization and the importance of understanding and living with others who are different. His own life places him in a uniquely good position to consider these themes.<br/>Maalouf&apos;s history of the Crusades through Arab eyes is world-shifting for those of us with European/Christian backgrounds who were brought up</span>
  <span id="freeText12993739916178499172" style="display:none">Amin Maalouf is one of my favourite writers. Born in Lebanon, he lives in France and writes in French. His fiction and nonfiction alike are concerned with tolerance, intolerance, culture and civilization and the importance of understanding and living with others who are different. His own life places him in a uniquely good position to consider these themes.<br />Maalouf's history of the Crusades through Arab eyes is world-shifting for those of us with European/Christian backgrounds who were brought up thinking of the crusaders as valiant heroes venturing for God in the Holy Land., like King Richard the Lionheart. The reality was far different. The motives of the European Crusaders varied greatly and always had to do with the balance of power in Europe itself. Militant popes were very good at stirring up war to support their own power bases and it often suited kings and princes to commit to an overseas adventure rather than sorting things out at home. And there was, of course, the passionate commitment to Christianity as a religion and source of hope that sent thousands of children and adults on their way to the Holy Land.<br />Maalouf's book reverses the familiar views, throws our preconceptions up in the air so that when they come down again the pattern of understanding is transformed.<br />A must read for anyone interested in the interactions between the Muslim and Christian worlds, past and present.</span>
  <a data-text-id="12993739916178499172" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

