    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4060686875" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1242654923208163985">Having read my share of European history, let me start by saying: the Muslims had better chroniclers. Both the Christians and the Muslims had their internal tensions at the time: the Catholics massacred the Eastern Orthodox when they had a chance, and the Shiites and Sunnis hated one another as much as they hated the infidels. There are crazy scenes of Franjs (as the Crusaders were called by the Crusaded Against) and jihadists facing off against other groupings of French and Arabs. There aren’t </span>
  <span id="freeText1242654923208163985" style="display:none">Having read my share of European history, let me start by saying: the Muslims had better chroniclers. Both the Christians and the Muslims had their internal tensions at the time: the Catholics massacred the Eastern Orthodox when they had a chance, and the Shiites and Sunnis hated one another as much as they hated the infidels. There are crazy scenes of Franjs (as the Crusaders were called by the Crusaded Against) and jihadists facing off against other groupings of French and Arabs. There aren’t many heroes to this tale of land-grabbing and treachery, but Saladin does come across well. He didn’t kill entire cities as they surrendered, and was a generous and tolerant man. Characters and battles are described in a lively manner by Maalouf, using original sources. If you like history and want to know more about the roots of conflict in Israel/ Palestine, this is an excellent choice.</span>
  <a data-text-id="1242654923208163985" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

